arrest_table = pandas.read_csv("http://www.hcbravo.org/IntroDataSci/misc/BPD_Arrests.csv")

arrest_table["race_new"] = arrest_table["race"]
arrest_table["sex_new"] = arrest_table["sex"]
arrest_table["race"] = arrest_table["race_new"]
arrest_table["sex"] = arrest_table["sex_new"]
arrest_table = arrest_table.drop('race_new', 1)
arrest_table = arrest_table.drop('sex_new', 1)

arrest_table = arrest_table[pandas.notnull(arrest_table["Location 1"])]

arrest_table["lat"], arrest_table["long"] = arrest_table["Location 1"].str.split(",").str
arrest_table["lat"] = arrest_table["lat"].str.replace("(", "").astype(float)
arrest_table["long"] = arrest_table["long"].str.replace(")", "").astype(float)

arrest_table.head()

ndata = arrest_table.sample(n=1000)

Define heapmap, racial circles, and teen circles¶

Colors are as follows:

Black : Red | White : Orange | Asian : Yellow | Hispanic: Purple | Indian : Blue | Unkown : green | Other : Crimson

Additionally there is the color Black to represent teenagers.

In [33]:
heat_data = [[row['lat'],row['long']] for index, row in ndata.iterrows()]
HeatMap(heat_data,radius=20).add_to(map_osm)



for index, row in ndata.iterrows():
    color=''
    if row['race'] == 'B':
        color='red'
    if row['race'] == 'W':
        color='orange'
    if row['race'] == 'A':
        color='yellow'
    if row['race'] == 'U':
        color='green'
    if row['race'] == 'I':
        color='blue'
    if row['race'] == 'H':
        color='purple'
    if row['race'] == np.nan:
        color='crimson'
    folium.Circle(
    radius=40,
    location=[row['lat'], row['long']],
    popup=row['incidentOffense'],
    color=color,
    fill=True,
).add_to(map_osm)

for index, row in teen_table.iterrows():
    color= 'black'
    folium.Circle(
    radius=40,
    location=[row['lat'], row['long']],
    popup=row['incidentOffense'],
    color=color,
    fill=True,
).add_to(map_osm)

Baltimore Crime¶

The Map:¶

This map reflects a sample (1000 Elements) of a very large dataset (over 100,000 elements) regarding the crime in Baltimore.

Through the use of smaller circles, and a heapmap we have been able to visualize the various places that have the highest concentration of crime. By using diffrent colored circles we have identified that most crimes done by people in similar racial groups been in very close distance from each other. There are also several locations in baltimore that have significant heat coloration, meaning that those places have a higher concentration of crime. This is especially true because as you move closer to the center of baltimore, the hues of the heat map get warmer.

In regards to teenagers (the black circles), they are most commonly found in these large areas of crime. Although there are a significant amount in those areas, it is also apparent that some teenagers have done crime in the less concentrated areas of crime, which shows that the highly concentrated crime is just one of many factors in teen crime.

While there is alot of data representing recording of crime in the city, there are some areas that lack any heat coloration or circles indicating crime. The data depicts that places like the area around Loyola University or Overlea have little to no crime; Suggesting that there is a chance that this data has not accurately recorded all cases of crime.
